The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification and handwriting recognition, which are both topics within computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on improving the efficiency of training and testing deep CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of sparsity to improve the performance of CNNs, which is a topic within artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
